subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Male (Novo Airão,
14-19 .vi. 1996
). Head. Dorsal part of the eye light brown with large ommatidia; ventral part of the eye dark brown to black, with small ommatidia. Subcallus dark brown to black, shiny; base of the antenna with silver pollinosity. Antenna dark brown to black: scape and pedicel with black hairs. Flagellum dark brown to black with golden pollinosity; basal flagellomere with dorsal spine reaching the third flagellomere. Face and parafacia dark brown to black, with black hairs and silver pollinosity best seen in frontal view. Gena and postgena dark brown to black, with silver pollinosity and black hairs. Palpus dark brown to black, with silver pollinosity and black hairs.

Measurements. (n = 1 , Novo Airão,
14-19 .vi. 1996
) Body length: 14.57mm . Wing length: 11.43mm .

Distribution.
Argentina
(
Formosa
); 
Brazil
(Amazonas, Mato Grosso, Pará); 
Colombia
; 
French Guiana
; 
Trinidad and Tobago
; 
Venezuela
